{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "frontend/package.json",
      "use": "@vercel/static-build",
      "config": {
        "distDir": "dist"
      }
    },
    {
      "src": "backend/server.js",
      "use": "@vercel/node"
    }
  ],
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/api/(.*)",
      "dest": "backend/server.js"
    },
    {
      "handle": "filesystem"
    },
    {
      "src": "/(.*)",
      "dest": "/index.html"
    }
  ]
}

/*
Short answer: vercel.json helps, but it does not fully solve the lag by itself.

What it fixes:

Correct Vercel routing/build behavior for your monorepo.
Sends /api/* to backend and serves frontend SPA correctly.
With the server.js export change, avoids one major runtime mismatch.*/